HEADWORD: Conglaciation
<hw>Con*gla`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>conglaciation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of changing
into ice, or the state of being converted to ice; a freezing;
congelation; also, a frost.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

